  "prompt": "How long does a high school basketball game usually last?",
  "response": "A high school basketball game typically lasts between **1.5 to 2 hours**, though the exact duration can vary based on several factors:\n\n1. **Regulation Play**:  \n   - The game is divided into **four 8-minute quarters** (32 minutes total).  \n   - The clock stops for fouls, timeouts, free throws, and other stoppages, extending real-time play.\n\n2. **Breaks and Halftime**:  \n   - **Halftime**: Usually **10\u201315 minutes**.  \n   - **Quarter Breaks**: 1\u20132 minutes between quarters (3 breaks total).  \n   - Timeouts: Each team has 3\u20135 full timeouts (1 minute each), adding 5\u201310+ minutes.\n\n3. **Overtime**:  \n   - Tied games go into **4-minute overtime periods**, each adding ~10\u201315 minutes with stoppages.\n\n**Key Variables**:  \n- Pace of play, foul frequency, and timeouts.  \n- Overtime can significantly extend the game (e.g., multiple OT periods).  \n\nIn summary, expect most games to wrap up in **1.5\u20132 hours**, with overtime pushing it closer to **2\u20132.5 hours** if needed.",
